35% markup for vendors


Thanks! Some updates:
1. Every product should have a shared product option of "vendor_id" in BigCommerce, the value of which should be the ID that is associated to the vendor on creation in the database. 
2. If the product exists (via exact name or sku match) for another vendor, the product should not be merged, but added as a new product and added with shared product option "duplicate" set as true.
3. For product brand and category, please add extra formatting and qualification to ensure the category or brand does not exist in any variant (different case, different spacing) before creating a new one. 
4.  Before the product data is sent to BigCommerce for insert - IF the vendor has the associated endpoint:
- Ensure all media associated with the product is attached (via MediaContentService endpoint - operation getMediaContent)
- All product configuration, decoration, and pricing data is associated (via PricingAndConfigurationService endpoint operations).
- Full inventory is accurate (via Inventory endpoint operation getInventoryLevels)
5. PricingAndConfigurationService endpoints are very important here. Each product will have available locations getAvailableLocations for customization. The customer can choose one or more of these locations when configuring a product to add to cart. Each selected location will have a number of decorations included, min and max decorations, and an array of the available decoration methods for that location. These are important because these affect the modifiers that will change the charge price of the product when added to cart based on the charges associated with the location, decoration and amount of decorations. So how location, decoration, and charge modifiers and option are set up on each product should be thought out and deliberately planned.
6. Some important data from the ProductData getProduct operation we want to ensure we are saving correctly: 
- Size - this should correlate to shared product option name "size" that is already setup in BigCommerce for the labelSizeEnum in promostandards
- LocationDecorationArray
- ProductKeywordArray (this should go into bigcommerce product field 'search_keywords')
- RelatedProductArray (should link to relatedProducts in BigCommerce)
- Price - all price data from any vendor API should be entered into "cost_price", and set up in bulk_pricing_rules as a % discount related to the percent of discount per tier for that vendor. The product default price should be % increase on the price provided by the vendor API - this should be dynamically set based on the default value for shared product option "product_cost_markup"'s value (which is currently 30).
7.  Prices on parts and and charges (PricingAndConfiguration PartPrice and Charge, ChargePrice objects) are very important to consider and should be set up as product modifiers, as these will change based on selected configuration options (selected part, location, decoration).



